{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-jsx","path":"/postgreSQL/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"DAEHUN GO"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"99d0701c-aca4-5ab4-9e48-dae2d984e31c","excerpt":"üèÜ¬†GOAL Gain a clear understanding of what PostgreSQL is. Explain how PostgreSQL differs from other RDBMS. Able to use PostgreSQL's key features. (custom data type, JSON type, etc...) Able to determin‚Ä¶","html":"<br>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"GOAL\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#GOAL\" aria-label=\"GOAL permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a>üèÜ¬†GOAL</h2>\n<ol>\n<li>Gain a clear understanding of what PostgreSQL is.</li>\n<li>Explain how PostgreSQL differs from other RDBMS.</li>\n<li>Able to use PostgreSQL's key features. (custom data type, JSON type, etc...)</li>\n<li>Able to determine which projects are suitable for PostgreSQL.</li>\n</ol>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"PostgreSQLÏù¥ÎûÄ\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#PostgreSQL%EC%9D%B4%EB%9E%80\" aria-label=\"PostgreSQLÏù¥ÎûÄ permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a>üëãüèª¬†PostgreSQLÏù¥ÎûÄ?</h2>\n<p>PostgreSQL is an open-source <strong>Object-Relational Database Management System</strong> that evolved from the Postgres project, which began at UC Berkeley in 1986.</p>\n<p>Currently, it is characterized by scalability, stability, and standards compliance, making it one of the most trusted databases worldwide.</p>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"-Why-Do-People-Choose-PostgreSQL\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#-Why-Do-People-Choose-PostgreSQL\" aria-label=\" Why Do People Choose PostgreSQL permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a>ü§î <strong>Why Do People Choose PostgreSQL?</strong></h2>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Open Source</strong> : Free to use with no license restrictions.</li>\n<li><strong>Powerful Data Intigrity</strong> : Provides stability and reliability through ACID cmpliance.</li>\n<li><strong>Various Features</strong> : Supports diverse data types and advanced query functions including JSON, XML, Arrays.</li>\n<li><strong>Extensibility</strong> : Easy to extend functionality through custom data type and extension modules.</li>\n<li><strong>Multi-platform Support</strong> : Able to run on various operating systems including Windows,\nmacOs and Linux</li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"Key-Differentiators-of-PostgreSQL-from-Other-RDBMS\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#Key-Differentiators-of-PostgreSQL-from-Other-RDBMS\" aria-label=\"Key Differentiators of PostgreSQL from Other RDBMS permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a>üî•¬†<strong>Key Differentiators of PostgreSQL from Other RDBMS</strong></h2>\n<p>PostgreSQL goes beyond the role of simple data store, offering features that are hard to find in other RDBMS:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><strong>Custom Data Types</strong>: Able to create custome data types according to their needs.</li>\n<li><strong>JSON and JSONB Data Types</strong>: Combines the advantages of relational and non-relational databases.</li>\n<li><strong>HStore</strong>: Able to store Key-Value data.</li>\n<li><strong>Dimensional Data Types</strong>: Supports demensional data types</li>\n<li><strong>Extensible Architecture</strong>: Users can extend PostgreSQL's core functionality through extension module like PostGIS, which is useful for handling geographic data.</li>\n</ol>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"-Experiencing-PostgreSQLs-Unique-Features\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#-Experiencing-PostgreSQLs-Unique-Features\" aria-label=\" Experiencing PostgreSQLs Unique Features permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a>üíª <strong>Experiencing PostgreSQL's Unique Features</strong></h2>\n<h3 id=\"1-Using-Various-Data-Types-Not-Found-in-Other-RDBMS\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#1-Using-Various-Data-Types-Not-Found-in-Other-RDBMS\" aria-label=\"1 Using Various Data Types Not Found in Other RDBMS permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a>1. Using Various Data Types Not Found in Other RDBMS</h3>\n<p>Scenario: IoT (Internet of Things) Device Management Platform</p>\n<p><strong>Special Data Types Used</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>UUID: Unique Device Identification</li>\n<li>JSONB: Flexible Device Configuration and Sensor Data</li>\n<li>INET: Network Information and IP Tracking</li>\n<li>Custom Composite Type: Location Information (Latitude, Longitude, Altitude)</li>\n<li>Enum: Device Status Management</li>\n<li>MONEY: Maintenance Cost Tracking</li>\n<li>Range Type: Device Age Tracking</li>\n<li>Timestamp with Time Zone</li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<p><strong>Creating Custom Data Type 1 (Enumerated Type)</strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sql\"><pre class=\"language-sql\"><code class=\"language-sql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">CREATE</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">TYPE</span> DEVICE_CONNECTIVITY_STATUS <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">ENUM</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n\t<span class=\"token string\">'online'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token string\">'offline'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token string\">'maintenance'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token string\">'error'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\t<span class=\"token string\">'decommissioned'</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"%EC%8A%A4%ED%81%AC%EB%A6%B0%EC%83%B7%202024-12-11%20%EC%98%A4%ED%9B%84%204.51.07.png\" alt=\"alt text\"></p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>Creating Custom Data Type 2 (<em>Composite Type)</em></strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sql\"><pre class=\"language-sql\"><code class=\"language-sql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">CREATE</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">TYPE</span> geo_location <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    latitude <span class=\"token keyword\">NUMERIC</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">7</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    longitude <span class=\"token keyword\">NUMERIC</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">10</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">7</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    altitude <span class=\"token keyword\">NUMERIC</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">7</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span><span class=\"token number\">2</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"%EC%8A%A4%ED%81%AC%EB%A6%B0%EC%83%B7%202024-12-11%20%EC%98%A4%ED%9B%84%204.55.31.png\" alt=\"alt text\"></p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>Creating a Table Using Various Data Types (UUID / JSONB / INET / MONEY / DATE / RANGE / CUSTOM)</strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sql\"><pre class=\"language-sql\"><code class=\"language-sql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">CREATE</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">TABLE</span> iot_devices <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- UUID for unique device identification</span>\n    device_id UUID <span class=\"token keyword\">PRIMARY</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">KEY</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">DEFAULT</span> gen_random_uuid<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Device Metadata using JSONB</span>\n    device_details JSONB <span class=\"token operator\">NOT</span> <span class=\"token boolean\">NULL</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Network Information using INET</span>\n    network_info INET<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Device Location using Custom Composite Type</span>\n    current_location geo_location<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Device Status using Custom Enum</span>\n    current_status device_connectivity_status<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Maintenance Costs using MONEY</span>\n    maintenance_cost MONEY<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Last Maintenance Date</span>\n    last_maintenance_date <span class=\"token keyword\">DATE</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Custom Range Type for Device Age Tracking</span>\n    device_age INT4RANGE\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"%EC%8A%A4%ED%81%AC%EB%A6%B0%EC%83%B7%202024-12-11%20%EC%98%A4%ED%9B%84%204.58.05.png\" alt=\"alt text\"></p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>Query Data</strong></p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sql\"><pre class=\"language-sql\"><code class=\"language-sql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">SELECT</span>\n    device_id<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Extracting from JSONB</span>\n    device_details<span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token string\">'manufacturer'</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> manufacturer<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    device_details<span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">></span><span class=\"token string\">'hardware_specs'</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token operator\">>></span><span class=\"token string\">'cpu'</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> cpu_type<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Using Enum</span>\n    current_status<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Network Information</span>\n    host<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>network_info<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> ip_address<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Location Details</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>current_location<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>latitude <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> device_latitude<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>current_location<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>longitude <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> device_longitude<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Maintenance Cost</span>\n    maintenance_cost<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n\n    <span class=\"token comment\">-- Device Age Range</span>\n    lower<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>device_age<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> min_age<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    upper<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>device_age<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> max_age\n<span class=\"token keyword\">FROM</span> iot_devic</code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"%EC%8A%A4%ED%81%AC%EB%A6%B0%EC%83%B7%202024-12-11%20%EC%98%A4%ED%9B%84%205.07.25.png\" alt=\"alt text\"></p>\n<br>\n<p>Using PostgreSQL allows for modeling complex real-world entities more accurately in databases through its support for various data types and custom data types.</p>\n<p>However, this flexibility can potentially violate normalization principles.</p>\n<p>Particularly with JSONB, data duplication can occur. Additionally, the flexibility in data type assignments poses risks to data consistency and integrity. Complex composite types can be difficult to index and may lead to performance degradation in large-scale databases.</p>\n<h3 id=\"2-Exploring-PostgreSQL-Extensions-PostGIS\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#2-Exploring-PostgreSQL-Extensions-PostGIS\" aria-label=\"2 Exploring PostgreSQL Extensions PostGIS permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a><strong>2. Exploring PostgreSQL Extensions (PostGIS)</strong></h3>\n<p>One of <strong>PostgreSQL's</strong> greatest strengths is its ability to extend core functionality through various <strong>extension modules</strong>. Among these, <strong>PostGIS</strong> stands out as a powerful tool for processing and analyzing spatial data, making it essential for map and location-based application development. Let's explore PostGIS use cases and experience PostgreSQL's extension capabilities by using its core features.</p>\n<h3 id=\"PostGIS-Use-Cases\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#PostGIS-Use-Cases\" aria-label=\"PostGIS Use Cases permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a><strong>PostGIS Use Cases</strong></h3>\n<p>PostGIS is widely used in the following areas:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Maps and Navigation Systems</strong>: Location-based services (LBS) for route calculations, distance measurements, etc.</li>\n<li><strong>Smart Cities</strong>: Spatial data analysis for urban planning and infrastructure management.</li>\n<li><strong>Environmental Analysis</strong>: Spatial analysis for land use and ecosystem conservation.</li>\n<li><strong>Business Analytics</strong>: Store location selection, customer distribution analysis, etc.</li>\n</ul>\n<br>\n<h3 id=\"PostGIS-Practice-Working-with-Simple-Spatial-Data\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#PostGIS-Practice-Working-with-Simple-Spatial-Data\" aria-label=\"PostGIS Practice Working with Simple Spatial Data permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a><strong>PostGIS Practice: Working with Simple Spatial Data</strong></h3>\n<p><strong>1. Activating PostGIS</strong></p>\n<p>First, we need to activate PostGIS in the PostgreSQL database. Let's create a new database and add the extension.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sql\"><pre class=\"language-sql\"><code class=\"language-sql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">CREATE</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">DATABASE</span> spatialdb<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\\c spatialdb\n<span class=\"token keyword\">CREATE</span> EXTENSION postgis<span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><strong>2. Storing Point Data</strong></p>\n<p>Let's store and query city locations.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sql\"><pre class=\"language-sql\"><code class=\"language-sql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">CREATE</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">TABLE</span> cities <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>\n    id <span class=\"token keyword\">SERIAL</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">PRIMARY</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">KEY</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    name <span class=\"token keyword\">VARCHAR</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token number\">100</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    location <span class=\"token keyword\">GEOMETRY</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token keyword\">Point</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">4326</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span>\n\n<span class=\"token keyword\">INSERT</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">INTO</span> cities <span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>name<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> location<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span>\n<span class=\"token keyword\">VALUES</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Vancouver'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> ST_SetSRID<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>ST_MakePoint<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">123.1216</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">49.2827</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">4326</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token string\">'Seattle'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> ST_SetSRID<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>ST_MakePoint<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span><span class=\"token operator\">-</span><span class=\"token number\">122.3321</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">47.6062</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> <span class=\"token number\">4326</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><img src=\"%EC%8A%A4%ED%81%AC%EB%A6%B0%EC%83%B7%202024-12-12%20%EC%98%A4%ED%9B%84%204.36.45.png\" alt=\"alt text\"></p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>3. Distance Calculation</strong></p>\n<p>Calculate the distance between two cities.</p>\n<div class=\"gatsby-highlight\" data-language=\"sql\"><pre class=\"language-sql\"><code class=\"language-sql\"><span class=\"token keyword\">SELECT</span>\n    a<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> city1<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    b<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> city2<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span>\n    ST_Distance<span class=\"token punctuation\">(</span>a<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>location::geography<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>location::geography<span class=\"token punctuation\">)</span> <span class=\"token keyword\">AS</span> distance_meters\n<span class=\"token keyword\">FROM</span> cities a<span class=\"token punctuation\">,</span> cities b\n<span class=\"token keyword\">WHERE</span> a<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Vancouver'</span> <span class=\"token operator\">AND</span> b<span class=\"token punctuation\">.</span>name <span class=\"token operator\">=</span> <span class=\"token string\">'Seattle'</span><span class=\"token punctuation\">;</span></code></pre></div>\n<p><code class=\"language-text\">ST_Distance</code> is a function provided by PostGIS that calculates the <strong>shortest distance</strong> between two spatial objects.</p>\n<p><img src=\"%EC%8A%A4%ED%81%AC%EB%A6%B0%EC%83%B7%202024-12-12%20%EC%98%A4%ED%9B%84%204.37.35.png\" alt=\"alt text\"></p>\n<br>\n<p><strong>4. Visualization</strong></p>\n<p>You can visually verify the above results using pgAdmin or GIS tools (QGIS). Through pgAdmin's \"View Data\" option, you can directly view spatial data on a map.</p>\n<p><img src=\"%EC%8A%A4%ED%81%AC%EB%A6%B0%EC%83%B7%202024-12-12%20%EC%98%A4%ED%9B%84%204.41.33.png\" alt=\"alt text\"></p>\n<br>\n<h2 id=\"Ô∏è-Disadvantages-of-PostgreSQL\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#%EF%B8%8F-Disadvantages-of-PostgreSQL\" aria-label=\"Ô∏è Disadvantages of PostgreSQL permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a>‚ö†Ô∏è <strong>Disadvantages of PostgreSQL</strong></h2>\n<p>While PostgreSQL offers powerful features, it also has several drawbacks:</p>\n<ol>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Steep Learning Curve</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Requires significant learning time to utilize extension modules and advanced features effectively.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Potential Data Integrity Issues</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Using JSONB and custom types can lead to reduced data consistency and integrity.</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Horizontal Scaling (Sharding) Limitations</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>PostgreSQL is fundamentally designed for single-node operations, requiring additional tools (like Citus) for distributed processing.</li>\n<li><del>As I haven't personally experienced this aspect, I plan to practice it later and add more content about it.</del></li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<br>\n<h3 id=\"-Conclusion\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#-Conclusion\" aria-label=\" Conclusion permalink\" class=\"heading-anchor before\"><svg xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/2000/svg\" width=\"15\" height=\"15\" viewBox=\"0 0 24 24\"><path d=\"M6.188 8.719c.439-.439.926-.801 1.444-1.087 2.887-1.591 6.589-.745 8.445 2.069l-2.246 2.245c-.644-1.469-2.243-2.305-3.834-1.949-.599.134-1.168.433-1.633.898l-4.304 4.306c-1.307 1.307-1.307 3.433 0 4.74 1.307 1.307 3.433 1.307 4.74 0l1.327-1.327c1.207.479 2.501.67 3.779.575l-2.929 2.929c-2.511 2.511-6.582 2.511-9.093 0s-2.511-6.582 0-9.093l4.304-4.306zm6.836-6.836l-2.929 2.929c1.277-.096 2.572.096 3.779.574l1.326-1.326c1.307-1.307 3.433-1.307 4.74 0 1.307 1.307 1.307 3.433 0 4.74l-4.305 4.305c-1.311 1.311-3.44 1.3-4.74 0-.303-.303-.564-.68-.727-1.051l-2.246 2.245c.236.358.481.667.796.982.812.812 1.846 1.417 3.036 1.704 1.542.371 3.194.166 4.613-.617.518-.286 1.005-.648 1.444-1.087l4.304-4.305c2.512-2.511 2.512-6.582.001-9.093-2.511-2.51-6.581-2.51-9.092 0z\"/></svg></a>‚≠ê <strong>Conclusion</strong></h3>\n<p>PostgreSQL's major advantage lies in its support for diverse and flexible data types (MONEY, RANGE, INET, JSONB, CUSTOM TYPE), allowing natural representation of complex real-world entities in the database. Additionally, PostgreSQL provides powerful extension modules like PostGIS, enabling advanced functionality beyond basic database features.</p>\n<p>However, PostgreSQL has clear limitations including a significant learning curve, schema-less data model challenges, and lack of built-in distributed processing capabilities. Therefore, before choosing PostgreSQL, consider the following questions:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Do you need complex data types, JSON support, and custom data types?</li>\n<li>Are you planning to utilize advanced spatial data processing (like PostGIS)?</li>\n<li>Is your environment capable of vertical scaling for large-scale data processing?</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you can answer these questions positively, PostgreSQL would be an excellent choice. Experience PostgreSQL's powerful features in your project! üöÄ</p>","frontmatter":{"title":"‚ùìPostgreSQL: Why Do Developers Choose It?","date":"December 30, 2024","update":"December 30, 2024","tags":["PostgreSql"],"series":"Tech"},"fields":{"slug":"/postgreSQL/","readingTime":{"minutes":5.9}}},"seriesList":{"edges":[{"node":{"id":"99d0701c-aca4-5ab4-9e48-dae2d984e31c","fields":{"slug":"/postgreSQL/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"‚ùìPostgreSQL: Why Do Developers Choose It?"}}}]},"previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/starting-sorting-algorithm/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"üóÇÔ∏è Sorting Algorithm"}},"next":null},"pageContext":{"id":"99d0701c-aca4-5ab4-9e48-dae2d984e31c","series":"Tech","previousPostId":"44e0eb2c-2a82-543b-87cc-f22d88025ed2","nextPostId":null}},"staticQueryHashes":[],"slicesMap":{}}